&lt;p&gt;Our Clinical Academy is expanding with a focus on developing therapy students and increasing our placement offer. We are currently supporting 50+ nursing apprentices and 19 occupational therapy apprentices with a view to further expansion into other professional areas in the next academic year.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for a Learning Environment Lead to work with our AHP Academy team. You will be required to work across the scope of the organisation but the post offers regular opportunities to work from home as well as from our main bases in Ashford and Maidstone. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will manage a small team working with our therapy services to increase the number of student placements, develop opportunities for apprenticeships and support our students in practice. You will need to work in partnership with Health Education England, clinical colleagues, and placement and apprenticeship providers to ensure students receive a quality experience whilst on clinical placement within the Trust.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will act as a role model, while supporting staff to maintain high standards of clinical practice, have the skills to encourage and facilitate others to implement best practice and new ways of working which improve patient outcome and experience.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are passionate about improving patient care and enhancing patient experience by encouraging and supporting frontline staff then this is the job for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews are scheduled for 23rd November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
